race.comment: DREAM STAR (11) just missed over 1400m here 10 days ago and stretches to the mile for the first time today. She looks a progressive filly who will relish getting out in trip judging by the way she closed off last time. Pike remains in the saddle from a good draw and she can go one better this time. PARISH PRINCE (1) was very good over 1500m here and should appreciate the slight rise to the mile third-up. Draw is a niggle, though he'll improve with that run under his belt and a forward showing is anticipated. PRETEY ROYAL (5) finished 3.2L off the winner at Ascot last start and comes back to the mile now. Not to be discounted. ARPIONE (4) is a big chance based on his latest effort at Bunbury.
